Rating: 4
I made this recipe once for a potluck and I have requests over and over for it. Its fairly easy and always a winner. I always use fresh nutmeg and I do think that makes a difference.

Rating: 1
I made this for Easter and it was not well received. My guests said I should have added brown sugar and I agreed. I doubled the bourbon and still didn't taste it whatsoever. fyi, it took about 20 minutes for the cream to reduce, and you need a big gratin dish to fit these in a single layer. I will not be making these again.

Rating: 4
This was a huge hit at yesterday's Thanksgiving gathering. Everyone wanted the recipe saying they never really liked yams or sweet potatoes because they were covered in sweet gunk. I used whole nutmeg and grated it over the top before baking. Just delicious!

