I have made this recipe for 4 years in a row for our Thanksgiving sweet potato side. In fact, I get requests every year to make these. Most men I know say they hate sweet potatoes but change their mind once they taste these

Rating: 4
Scrumptious! We made this with pork shoulder and purple cabbage cole slaw for a Bourbon Heritage Month Party in September. People are still asking me for the recipe!

Rating: 4
Despite the other reviews, I thought this dish was delightful. I doubled the Burbon (cause that's the kinda gal I am!) - and I used Jim Beam, which has a distinct flavor as far as I'm concerned. It worked well with the sweetness of the potatoes. Mine were not significantly mushy - I ate it all up & got rave reviews. I served this with part of a thanksgiving dinner & was a nice variation on more typical ways to prepare sweet potatoes. I'll make this again.

